entry.content:
Now @JniType can annotate the return type of @NativeMethods methods or

the parameter of an @CalledByNative method and it will handle the

conversions in either direction (i.e. std::string <-> JavaRef).

of conversion more easily.

- Converted params are now just a reference instead of a move target

(i.e. std::string& for @JniType("std::string")).

- Improved Jni Zero BUILD.gn documentation and added a section about

@JniType and conversion functions.

entry.title: [AvatarButton] Intro to refactoring the state management
entry.content:
Intrdouce the concept of StateManager and StateProvider.

StateProvider would be linked to an enum value that would show it's

priority compared to other StateProviders.

StateManager would contain all possible states and be able to return

the current state that is active and with the highest priority.



The goal of this design is to have each State manage itself with

the information it needs. Also each State would be completely

independent from another one. It would only have to mark itself as

active or not, for the StateManager to be able to return the correct

active state at each time. Potentially multiple states could be

active at the same time, but only the highest priority one would be

used.



This way each state would be properly scoped and managing itself. It

would be easy to introduce a new state, just by giving it's right

priority through the list in the enum, and a way to activate itself.



Currently, not all the states were migrated to use this logic, so

additional code is needed to make sure the behavior is not altered

during the changes.



In future CLs:

- Make the states be able to request visual updates when their

active state is potentially being changed.

- Adapt the rest of the states to follow this logic.

- [Not sure about this one]: Potentially the StateProvider would be

able to provide more information as well, such as the Text or Color

directly.

CameraFrameVideoHandler calculates and caches the texture target that it

should use. However, there is no need to do this caching:

gpu::GetBufferTextureTarget(), always contains the same information

computed by the browser

where it is used. This paves the way for a followup that instead obtains

the texture target from the ClientSharedImage that is available at that

usage point.

entry.title: Revert "Fix CHIPS for WebView when 3PCs are not enabled"
entry.content:
This reverts commit cda963bec2af9b0f2abbef5e7aa672d9171b9848.



Reason for revert: Looks like this is introducing a performance regression (see crbug.com/324328158). It is likely caused by the std::copy_if. It could also be happening if the performance tests are not enabling 3PCs in the first place because then we'd be causing more work to happen than what was happening previously.



Original change's description:

> Fix CHIPS for WebView when 3PCs are not enabled

>

> If an Android developer disables 3PCs in their app, paritioned cookies

> will not be returned. The root cause of this is that WebView uses its

> own settings for cookies from the rest of Chromium.

>

> The behaviour of Chromium is that partitioned cookies are still returned

> when 3PCs are disabled so we are matching that.

>

> Because permissions apply at the level of BrowserContext for the rest of

> Chromium, we have to do an awkward work around here where we

> optimistically retrieve all cookies, and then filter out the non

> partitioned cookies. This is because we have no way of telling the lower

> layers that this is the behaviour we want for _this_ WebView. There may

> be a slight performance impact here but hopefully not a large one since

> apps that have 3PCs disabled wouldn't be setting them in the first

> place. The real issue is more around apps changing this setting at

> runtime.

>

entry.title: [iOS] Make Docking Promo inactive time thresholds Finchable.
entry.content:
The Docking Promo display trigger criteria depend on two thresholds when

determining whether or not to display the promo:



1. For users no older than 2 days, whether or not they were inactive in

the last 24hr.



2. For users no older than 14 days, whether or not they were inactive in

the last 72hr.



To ease experimentation, the 24hr/72hr thresholds should be controlled

via server-side Finch to ease testing by introducing potentially shorter

threshold times, if needed.



This change does the following:

- Introduces new server-side Finch params for the 24hr/72hr thresholds

- Updates CanShowDockingPromo() to evaluate TimeDelta hours (instead of

days).

entry.content:
OOB checks for operators ++/--/+=/-= aren't optional, as shifting a pointer to another slot without updating ref-counts would affect the integrity of the algorithm.



OOB checks for operator+/operator- are optional, because the resulting pointer will be written to a new raw_ptr<>, which will update ref-count properly. Even more so for operator[], which don't modify or create any pointers.



This CL is expected to be a no-op.

entry.title: [Blink] Refine GpuCanvasContext WebGPU SharedImage usage reference
entry.content:
GpuCanvasContext copies WebGPU textures to CanvasResourceProviders'

backing SharedImages via the WebGPU interface:



* Associating the backing SharedImage with a destination WebGPU texture

* Copying the source WebGPU texture into the destination WebGPU texture

* Disassociating the destination WebGPU texture with the backing

SharedImage (on the service side, this ends the Dawn access that was

initiated by the association)



It currently CHECKs that the backing SharedImage has

WEBGPU_READ | WEBGPU_WRITE usage, but for this purpose, the SI need

have only WEBGPU_WRITE usage.

entry.title: [fuchsia] Fix update_sdk.py to handle version:-prefix
entry.content:
DEPS mistakenly specifies the "fuchsia_version" with the CIPD

tag's "version:" prefix included in the version value. This breaks

the update_sdk.py scripts check of the version against the current

SDK version as per the "manifest.json", causing update_sdk.py to

always re-download the SDK.



Fix the update_sdk.py script to add the "version:" prefix to the

command-line version argument to create the CIPD tag.



Support for broken callers passing "version:" prefixed values is

temporarily retained.



The script is also updated to validate that the downloaded SDK

reports the expected version, so that similar mismatches will be

caught in future. The "Downloading Fuchsia SDK" message in DEPS is

corrected, and some log-spam is removed from the Fuchsia system-images

download script.

entry.title: [iOS][Waffle] Add default search engine icon
entry.content:
It is possible to have no embedded icons for prepopulated search

engines in EEA countries. This happen when the user select

a prepopulated search engine outside of EEA counties, and then switch

to a EEA countries. The selected search engine is still part of

prepopulated search engine, but it doesn't have an embedded icons.



To avoid DCHECK/CHECK issues, the temporary solution is to use

`default_world_favicon` icon. This patch will be merged in M123.



For M124, the code will be update to download icon if it doesn't exist.
